<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,1038,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Legs. Apical tarsomere with arolium, claws without tooth on inner margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Metasoma. Petiole slightly coriaceous, weakly shiny, with several fine punctures. Metasomal segment smooth and shiny, with several tiny punctures. Relative length of petiole: hindtarsomere I: II: III = 28: 41: 20: 15. Genitalia as figs 11, 12.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,414,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,549,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,549,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[359,426,332,357]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">China</collectingCountry>
(
